docs: Update README.md
- Added "Aidan" to the list of words for the spellcheck in the vscode settings - The README.md and a few more source files have been translated to Chinese - Provided an example configuration for Azure OpenAI with gpt-4o in the default config.yml - Corrected an inconsistency in the prompt descriptions of Villager personalities - Added the capability for a custom topic while AI chatting - Plugin commands for initiating talking, clearing conversation, and ending conversation with villagers were translated into Chinese.

chore: prompt engineering
- Changed wording from "trade" to "transaction" in the trading rules. - Incorporated reasoning around denial of items not on the list in the trading rules. - Villagers can now buy player items related to their profession. - Villagers can occasionally talk about seeing Endermen and strange buildings (player-made) and villagers disappearing in their conversations. - Updated the storytelling theme to be specifically aligned with the "Minecraft" style in the conversations. - All actions performed by villagers are now clearly prefixed with `ACTION:` - Added an example (`ACTION:SHAKE_HEAD`) for execution of an action in the conversation. - Updated the term "Minecraft" to be in quotes, indicating the context of a game's name in restrictions.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: refine item specifications for village traders
- Detailed items sold by the Armorer by specifying the type of armor material such as chainmail, iron, diamond - Add "painting" to the list of items sold by the Shepherd - Specified the type of tools sold by the Toolsmith such as stone, iron, diamond - Detailed weapons sold by the Weaponsmith, specifically iron and diamond axes and swords
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>
